                    <p>3</p>
                    </td>
                    </tr>
                    </tbody>
                    </table>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p>
                    <p>Tumor regression should be assessed only in the primary tumor; lymph node metastases should not be included in the assessment.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p>
                    <p>Acellular pools of mucin in specimens following neoadjuvant therapy are considered to represent completely eradicated tumor and are not used to assign pT stage or counted as positive lymph nodes.</p>
					</div>
